  "text": "Routine systems that monitor exposure to relevant topics could be constructed to identify locations where misinformation or lowquality evidence is over-represented in the news media, and guide public health interventions to amplify high-quality evidence and guide social media interventions [CITATION_1] . More precise identification of the safety concerns, misinformation, and conspiracies that are important to a segment of the public could provide a basis from which to construct targeted and cost-effective news and social media based interventions.",
